{LA PARTIDA MÁS LOCA DE MIGUEL SANTOS} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. cxd5
exd5 5. Bf4 c5 6. e3 c4 $6 {I never believed in avoiding center fight-why not
normal Nc6?} (6... Nc6) 7. Nge2 ({Here White tried to win a pawn} 7. Bxb8 Bxc3+
8. bxc3 Rxb8 9. Qa4+ b5 10. Qxa7 Qd6 11. a3 (11. Be2 Nf6 12. Bf3 O-O 13. Ne2
Bd7 14. Qa5 Ra8 15. Qb4 Qc6 16. O-O Ra4 {with counterplay, Hoang,T (2472)
-Batsiashvili,N (2473) Chakvi 2015}) 11... Ne7 12. Nf3 O-O 13. Qc5 Qxc5 14.
dxc5 Ra8 15. Nd4 Bd7 16. Be2 Rfc8 17. Kd2 Rxc5 18. Rhb1 {1/2 (18) Gundavaa,B 
(2516)-Andreikin,D (2727) Kazan 2013}) 7... Nc6 8. a3 Ba5 {[#]} 9. b4 $5 ({
Possible was immediate development of the other side} 9. h4 Nge7 10. g3 Bg4 11.
Bg2) 9... cxb3 10. Qxb3 Nge7 11. Rc1 O-O 12. Ng1 $6 {Courageous move!More
safer would be} (12. h4 h6 13. f3) 12... Nf5 (12... Bf5 13. Nf3 Ng6 14. Bg3 Rc8
15. Be2) 13. Nf3 Qf6 14. Be5 $5 ({It was funny repetition} 14. Bg3 Qh6 15. Bf4
Qf6 16. Bg3 Qh6) 14... Nxe5 15. Nxe5 Qh6 {[#] After this agressive move starts
completely uncontrolled  strikes.} 16. Qxd5 Nxe3 $1 17. Qxa5 Nxf1 18. Ne2 Nxh2
19. Kd1 Be6 20. Rc3 b6 ({It was better to start Kings hunting} 20... Rac8 21.
Nf3 Qg6 22. Rxh2 Qb1+ 23. Kd2 Qb2+ 24. Ke3 Rce8) 21. Qb4 a5 22. Qb2 a4 {[#]}
23. Nf3 $5 ({If White would like draw ,he would play} 23. Qd2 Qxd2+ 24. Kxd2
Ng4 25. Nxg4 Bxg4 26. Rb1) 23... Bb3+ 24. Rxb3 axb3 25. Rxh2 Qd6 26. Qxb3 ({
Safer would be} 26. Rh3 Rxa3 27. Ne5) 26... Rxa3 27. Qc2 h6 28. Rh5 Ra1+ 29.
Kd2 Rfa8 ({Not bad was} 29... Qa3) 30. Rb5 R1a2 (30... Rf1 $142) 31. Rb2 Qe6
32. Nc3 Rxb2 33. Qxb2 Qg4 34. Ke2 Qxg2 35. Nd5 Re8+ {[#]} 36. Ne3 {Suddenly
two Knights defends perfectily the King and pawn d4 will run forward!} Qg6 37.
d5 h5 38. Qb5 f5 $2 ({Such pawn has to be stopped at any price} 38... Rd8) 39.
d6 {[#]} f4 $2 ({Only chance was to find draw in some end like this} 39...
Rxe3+ 40. Kxe3 Qxd6 41. Qxf5 Qc5+) 40. d7 Rd8 41. Qd5+ Kf8 42. Ne5 Qf6 43. Nc2
$1 {With unstoppable Nd4 which will create all deadly threas.} f3+ 44. Ke3 1-0

