{IMPORTANTE VICTORIA DE DAVID ANTÓN} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5.
h3 Nbd7 6. Be3 e5 7. d5 Nc5 8. Qc2 a5 9. g4 c6 10. g5 {New interesting
idea!Usual move is} (10. Nf3 cxd5 11. cxd5 O-O 12. Be2 Ne8 13. g5 Bd7 14. h4 a4
15. Nd2 Rc8 16. b4 axb3 17. axb3 f5 18. f3 Rf7 19. Qb2 Qb6 20. O-O Bf8 21. b4
Nd3 22. Bxb6 Nxb2 23. Rfc1 Ng7 24. Be3 Nh5 {with sharp play,Yankelevich,L 
(2443)-Jurcik,M (2497) Balatonszarszo 2017}) 10... Nh5 11. O-O-O cxd5 12. Nxd5
O-O {[#]} 13. Bxc5 $1 {After this super strategical decision White will
dominate in the center.} dxc5 14. h4 $5 ({It is doubtful that Black will have
some real compensation for the Queen} 14. Nf6+ Bxf6 15. Rxd8 Bxd8 16. h4 a4 17.
Bh3 Bxh3 18. Nxh3 Ng7 19. Rd1 Ne6 20. Rd5) 14... Bg4 15. Be2 Bxe2 16. Nxe2 Ra6
{[#]} 17. Ng3 ({Anton decided not to accept this Queen sac at all as matter of
principle!} 17. Nf6+ Bxf6 18. Rxd8 Bxd8 19. Rd1 Ng7 20. Rd7 Ne6) 17... Nxg3 18.
fxg3 Kh8 19. Qd2 {Preparing h4-h5.} f6 20. Kb1 Rd6 21. gxf6 ({Or} 21. g4 fxg5
22. hxg5 Rf4 23. Qh2) 21... Bxf6 22. h5 Bg5 23. Qc3 Re8 24. hxg6 Rxg6 25. Rdf1
b6 26. Rf7 Rg7 27. Qf3 Reg8 {[#]} 28. Rf5 Qd6 29. Rh3 a4 30. a3 Bd8 31. Kc2 b5
$1 {At least Black  decided to counterstrike ,but his power is very mild.} 32.
cxb5 Qd7 33. Nc3 ({Simpler was} 33. b6 Qe6 34. Rhh5) 33... Ba5 34. Qd3 Qd4 {[#]
} 35. Qxd4 {Black sacrifices another pawn,but it is all too late.} exd4 36.
Nxa4 c4 37. b6 Be1 38. Nc5 d3+ 39. Kd1 Bxg3 40. e5 $1 Bh4 {[#]} 41. Rxh4 $1 {
Carefully calculated Kings raid wins immediately.} Rg1+ 42. Kd2 R8g2+ 43. Kc3
Rc1+ 44. Kb4 Rxb2+ 45. Ka5 {Y el rey negro pronto recibirá mate} 1-0

