{LA MEJOR PARTIDA DEL CAMPEÓN} {It was the best game of the Champion.He used
here his old weapon against Paulsen.} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6
5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Be3 a6 7. Qd2 Nf6 8. O-O-O Bb4 9. f3 O-O (9... Ne5 10. Nb3 b5 11.
Qe1 Be7 12. f4 Ng6 13. e5 Ng4 14. Ne4 O-O 15. Bc5 Bb7 16. h3 Nh6 17. Bxe7 Nxe7
18. Bd3 Nd5 19. Qd2 f6 20. exf6 Nxf6 21. Rhe1 Nf5 22. Nec5 {with serious
advantage, Saric,I (2637)-Djukic,N (2486) Sarajevo 2011}) 10. g4 b5 11. g5 Nh5
12. Kb1 Rb8 13. Nxc6 dxc6 ({To big advantage in endgame leads} 13... Qxc6 14.
Bh3 Bxc3 15. Qxc3 Qxc3 16. bxc3) {[#]} 14. f4 ({Not overactive} 14. e5 $6 Bb7
15. a3 Rfd8 16. Bd3 Be7 17. Qf2 c5 18. Rhe1 Ba8 19. f4 b4 20. axb4 cxb4 21. Na4
b3 22. Bb6 bxc2+ 23. Bxc2 Rxd1+ 24. Rxd1 Qc4 {with sharp play, Al Modiahki,M 
(2585)-Ashwin,J (2413) Subic Bay 2009}) 14... c5 ({Another option is possble
too} 14... e5 15. f5 Bb7 16. Be2 Nf4 17. Bf3 c5 18. Qd6 Qxd6 19. Rxd6 c4 20.
Rdd1 {with slight edge, Short,N (2706)-Satyapragyan,S (2439) Kolkata 2009}) 15.
Be2 g6 16. Bxh5 gxh5 17. f5 Bb7 {[#]} 18. g6 $5 {Looks logical and human to
open the Kings position,but engine way is a bit strange} (18. Bf4 e5 19. Bg3
Bxe4 20. Rhf1 {with advantage,}) 18... fxg6 19. fxg6 Bxc3 $6 ({White kept
better chances after} 19... hxg6 20. Qg2 Bxc3 21. bxc3 Rf6 22. Qg5) 20. gxh7+
Kxh7 21. Qxc3 Bxe4 22. Rhg1 Rf5 {[#]} ({Strong attack was developed after} 
22... Rf3 23. Rg5 Bg6 24. Rxc5 Qg7 25. Rc7 Rf7 26. Rxf7 Qxf7 27. Bc1) 23. Bc1
$1 {Beautiful technical idea to coordinate attack Queen and Bishop battery.}
Rf3 24. Qd2 Kh8 25. b3 $1 {Bishop can work on both diagonals!} Rbf8 26. Qh6+
Bh7 {[#]} (26... Qh7 27. Bb2+) 27. Rd7 $1 {Win is possible in many ways.} (27.
Bb2+ e5 28. Rde1 $18) 1-0

