{LA MEJOR PARTIDA DEL TORNEO} {It was probably best game of the Championship,
but Saric  was not deeply affected by this loss!} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6
4. Nc3 e6 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bxf6 Qxf6 7. e3 g6 8. Be2 Bg7 {Wojtaszek played this
position few times,now he is prepared really well.} 9. O-O O-O ({White can
start minority attck after} 9... Nd7 10. cxd5 exd5 11. b4) 10. Ne5 ({Usually
White opened the center here} 10. e4) 10... Nd7 11. f4 Qe7 ({Passive ,but
playable waselimination of this strong knight} 11... Nxe5 12. fxe5 Qe7 13. Qc2
Bd7 14. a3 f5 15. c5) 12. Qb3 Nxe5 ({White kept  advantage after} 12... g5 13.
g3 Nxe5 14. fxe5 f6 15. exf6 Bxf6 16. Rf2) 13. fxe5 Bd7 {[#]} 14. cxd5 ({
It was necessary to calculate carefully} 14. Qxb7 Rab8 (14... Rfb8 15. Qc7 Rxb2
16. Rab1) 15. Qxa7 (15. Qa6 Rxb2 16. Qxa7) 15... Ra8 16. Qb7 Rfb8 17. Qc7 Rc8
18. Qd6 $2 Qd8) 14... cxd5 15. e4 $1 {The most energetic treatment.} dxe4 ({
Saric did not like to have weakness on d5 for long time} 15... Bc6 16. exd5
exd5 17. Rae1 Rae8 18. Bf3) 16. Nxe4 Bc6 17. Nf6+ Bxf6 18. Rxf6 ({Black would
suffer even in Rooks end} 18. exf6 Qd6 19. Qe3 Qd5 20. Bf3 Qg5 21. Qxg5 hxg5
22. Bxc6 bxc6 23. Rac1 Rfb8 24. Rf2 Rd8 25. Rc4) 18... Rad8 19. Rd1 Rd7 20. h4
Rfd8 21. Qc3 Qf8 22. a3 Qg7 23. Rf4 {[#]} g5 $2 {Nobody forced this weakening
move.} ({Here and before it was necessary to build passive defence like} 23...
a6 24. Rdf1 Rc7 25. Qe3 Rdd7) 24. hxg5 hxg5 25. Rg4 f5 26. exf6 Qxf6 27. Rf1
Qh6 {[#]} 28. d5 $1 {Opening the position means start of decisive attack on
the Kings side.} Bxd5 29. Rf6 Qh5 ({Or} 29... Qg7 30. Qe5) 30. Rg3 Qh7 31. Bd3
Be4 32. Rxg5+ Rg7 33. Rxg7+ Qxg7 (33... Kxg7 34. Rf4+) 34. Bxe4 1-0

